      <hedline>
        <hl1>Corrections</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Correction of May 28 article on US Senate race in New York; Republican Rick Lazio supports Brady Bill requiring background checks (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>A front-page article yesterday about the United States Senate race in New York referred incorrectly to the views of the Republican candidate, Rick A. Lazio, on gun control. While he opposes a proposal made by his opponent, Hillary Rodham Clinton, to register new handguns and license new gun users, he supports the Brady Bill, which requires background checks for gun buyers, and a ban on some forms of assault weapons. He does not oppose all forms of gun control.</p>
      </block>
